{"id":"faithful","term":"Faithful","source":"Easton's Bible Dictionary (M.G. Easton, 1897)","html":"<p>As a designation of Christians, means full of faith, trustful, and not simply trustworthy (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 10:45\">Acts 10:45</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Acts 16:1\">16:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"2 Corinthians 6:15\">2 Cor. 6:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Colossians 1:2\">Col. 1:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 4:3\">1 Tim. 4:3</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 1:12\">12</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 5:16\">5:16</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Genesis 6:2\">6:2</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Titus 1:6\">Titus 1:6</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Ephesians 1:1\">Eph. 1:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Corinthians 4:17\">1 Cor. 4:17</a>, etc.).</p>\n<p>It is used also of God’s word or covenant as true and to be trusted (<a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 119:86\">Ps. 119:86</a>, <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Psalms 119:138\">138</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Isaiah 25:1\">Isa. 25:1</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"1 Timothy 1:15\">1 Tim. 1:15</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 21:5\">Rev. 21:5</a>; <a class=\"ref\" data-ref=\"Revelation 22:6\">22:6</a>, etc.).</p>\n\u0000","refs":["Acts 10:45","Acts 16:1","2 Corinthians 6:15","Colossians 1:2","1 Timothy 4:3","Genesis 1:12","Genesis 5:16","Genesis 6:2","Titus 1:6","Ephesians 1:1","1 Corinthians 4:17","Psalms 119:86","Psalms 119:138","Isaiah 25:1","1 Timothy 1:15","Revelation 21:5","Revelation 22:6"]}